FBIS3-8471 "dreeu047_i_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-047 Document Type:Daily Report 10 Mar 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serb Attack Kills Seven in Bihac, Maglaj LD1003084194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 0700 GMT 10 Mar 94 LD1003084194 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Language: Serbo-Croatian Article Type:BFN [Text] The region of Bihac remains the focus of aggressor's offensive. Throughout yesterday the aggressor used howitzers, in particular, and tanks to pound the area. Three civilians were killed and dozens injured. The aggressor also attacked the defense lines and threatened the Bihac-Cazin road. Forces of the so-called "autonomasi" [anti-Izetbegovic forces] have been also been very active. Attacks on Maglaj were of a slightly lesser ferocity but there were civilian fatalities nevertheless. Chetnik snipers, howitzers and mortars killed four civilians. Infantry attacks were repulsed. The humanitarian situation in the town is exceptionally difficult.
